PMID== 7898461
TI  == clostridial adp-ribosylating toxins: effects on atp and gtp-binding proteins.
AB  == the actin cytoskeleton appears to be as the cellular target of various clostridial adp-ribosyltransferases which have been described during recent years. clostridium botulinum c2 toxin, clostridium perfringens iota toxin and clostridium spiroforme toxin adp-ribosylate actin monomers and inhibit actin polymerization. clostridium botulinum exoenzyme c3 and clostridium limosum exoenzyme adp-ribosylate the low-molecular-mass gtp-binding proteins of the rho family, which participate in the regulation of the actin cytoskeleton. adp-ribosylation inactivates the regulatory rho proteins and disturbs the organization of the actin cytoskeleton.
