PMID== 8223953
TI  == gelsolin-actin complex is target for adp-ribosylation by clostridium botulinum c2 toxin in intact human neutrophils.
AB  == the gelsolin-actin complex was adp-ribosylated by clostridium botulinum c2 toxin  and clostridium perfringens iota toxin in lysates of human platelets and human neutrophils. when [32p]orthophosphate-labelled human neutrophils were treated with c. botulinum c2 toxin, [32p]adp-ribosylated gelsolin-actin was precipitated  with anti-gelsolin antibody. stimulation of neutrophils by formyl-methionine-leucine-phenylalanine decreased the interaction of gelsolin with adp-ribosylated actin in toxin-treated cells. the data indicate that the gelsolin-actin complex is a pathophysiological substrate for actin-adp-ribosylating toxins.
